summary.name: Gapminder Health and Income
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about countries' income, health, population, and region.

properties.description: Average income per person in the country
Average health index of the country
Geographical region the country belongs to

goals.question: What is the relationship between income and health?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of income vs health
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a correlation between income and health. We can see if countries with higher income have better health outcomes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of income across regions?
goals.visualization: Box plot of income by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the income distribution across different regions. We can see if there are any outliers or if there are significant differences in income between regions.

goals.question: What is the distribution of health across regions?
goals.visualization: Box plot of health by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the health distribution across different regions. We can see if there are any outliers or if there are significant differences in health outcomes between regions.

goals.question: What is the relationship between population and income?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of population vs income
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a correlation between population and income. We can see if countries with larger populations have higher incomes or if there is no relationship between the two.

goals.question: What is the relationship between region and health?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of average health by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there are any significant differences in health outcomes between regions. We can see which regions have the highest and lowest average health scores.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='income', y='health', hue='region', palette='deep')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income and health?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Income')
    plt.ylabel('Health')
    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income', data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of income across regions?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Income')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='health', data=data, palette='Set2')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of health across regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Health Index')

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_health_by_region = data.groupby('region')['health'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='region', y='health', data=avg_health_by_region, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between region and health?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Average Health')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right', labels=avg_health_by_region['region'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
